	<entry>
		<id>http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Lake&amp;diff=40472</id>
		<title>Lake</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Lake&amp;diff=40472"/>
		<updated>2022-06-25T15:20:43Z</updated>

		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Mrstickman1997: Lakes can be dangerous sometimes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;lt;noinclude&amp;gt;{{Map&amp;lt;/noinclude&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;lt;includeonly&amp;gt;{{row/Map1&amp;lt;/includeonly&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 |name=lake&lt;br /&gt;
 |glyph=&amp;lt;nowiki&amp;gt;#&amp;lt;/nowiki&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 |color=c_blue&lt;br /&gt;
 |seecost=1&lt;br /&gt;
 |extras=no_extras&lt;br /&gt;
}}&amp;lt;noinclude&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Lakes are colossal bodies of deep water, they are much bigger than [[river]]s, and can contain isolated structures such as island [[prison]]s, lighthouse islands, etc.&lt;br /&gt;
It is best accessed via [[Vehicles|boat]], or by [[fish]] mutants.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
While rich in fish, water and occasional structures, lakes can also rarely contain dangerous monsters such as the dreaded [[jawed terror]].&lt;/div&gt;</summary>
		<author><name>Mrstickman1997</name></author>
		
	</entry>
	<entry>
		<id>http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Skills&amp;diff=40471</id>
		<title>Skills</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Skills&amp;diff=40471"/>
		<updated>2022-06-25T15:17:49Z</updated>

		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Mrstickman1997: /* Swimming */ It's now called Athletics...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
{{tocr}}&lt;br /&gt;
Skills are raised upon practice (combat, [[crafting]], [[tools|tool]] usage). Practice is multiplied by your current focus / 100; therefore focus pool level above 100 provides a bonus to the amount of skill gained, while amounts below 100 provide a penalty. The focus pool is not capped, but it requires higher morale to increase to higher levels, every few turns your focus is increased or decreased depending on your current morale. You can increase the speed at which you gain focus by increasing your morale.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
As of {{InlineVer|0.C}}, performing a crafting or construction task of certain difficulty can only bring your skill to (difficulty*1.25)+1, rounded down. For example, boiling water and digging pits (skill 0) will only bring cooking and construction to 1. Even the easiest task will still stop skill rust.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
{| class=&amp;quot;wikitable&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;
|+ Skill gaining through craft&lt;br /&gt;
|-&lt;br /&gt;
! Craft Difficulty !! Maximum skill level&lt;br /&gt;
|-&lt;br /&gt;
| 0 || 1&lt;br /&gt;
|-&lt;br /&gt;
| 1 || 2&lt;br /&gt;
|-&lt;br /&gt;
| 2 || 3&lt;br /&gt;
|-&lt;br /&gt;
| 3 || 4&lt;br /&gt;
|-&lt;br /&gt;
| 4 || 6&lt;br /&gt;
|-&lt;br /&gt;
| 5 || 7&lt;br /&gt;
|-&lt;br /&gt;
| 6 || 8&lt;br /&gt;
|-&lt;br /&gt;
| 7 || 9&lt;br /&gt;
|-&lt;br /&gt;
| 8 || 11&lt;br /&gt;
|-&lt;br /&gt;
| 9 || 12&lt;br /&gt;
|-&lt;br /&gt;
| 10 || 13&lt;br /&gt;
|}&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
You can also increase skill levels by reading [[books]] or being taught by [[NPC]]s. Note that reading skill books costs focus, but being trained does not.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The Melee and Firearms skill will improve both accuracy and damage of their respective weapons, but not as much as the weapon's main skill (handguns, cutting weapons etc.)&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
[[Stats]] will also affect a player's skills by making them more/less effective depending on the value of the stat. Dexterity will affect the accuracy and effectiveness for most attacks. Strength will affect the damage of all melee attacks. Intelligence can improve certain skills, increase the rate of learning, and reduce the time needed to read a  book. Perception can increase a player's accuracy for ranged attacks, and increases trap detection. &amp;lt;noinclude&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
== Skill Rust ==&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
{| border=&amp;quot;0&amp;quot; cellpadding=&amp;quot;3&amp;quot; class=&amp;quot;va-table&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;border-collapse: collapse; float:left; margin: 0.2em 1em&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;
|- style=&amp;quot;background-color:lightgreen&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;
! style=&amp;quot;border: 1px dashed darkgreen&amp;quot; colspan=&amp;quot;2&amp;quot; | Degradation&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;scale&lt;br /&gt;
|- style=&amp;quot;background-color:lightgreen&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;
! style=&amp;quot;border: 1px dashed darkgreen&amp;quot; | Level&lt;br /&gt;
! style=&amp;quot;border: 1px dashed darkgreen&amp;quot; | &amp;lt;abbr title=&amp;quot;10 turns = 1 minute&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Turn&amp;lt;/abbr&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;lt;!-- &lt;br /&gt;
int forgetCap = std::min(level, 7);&lt;br /&gt;
return 32768 / int(std::pow(2.0, double(forgetCap - 1)));&lt;br /&gt;
~~~&lt;br /&gt;
32768 / 2^(7-1) = 512&lt;br /&gt;
--&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
|- style=&amp;quot;border: 1px dashed darkgreen&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;
|style=&amp;quot;text-align:center&amp;quot;|1&lt;br /&gt;
|style=&amp;quot;text-align:right&amp;quot;|32768&lt;br /&gt;
|- style=&amp;quot;border: 1px dashed darkgreen&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;
|style=&amp;quot;text-align:center&amp;quot;|2&lt;br /&gt;
|style=&amp;quot;text-align:right&amp;quot;|16384&lt;br /&gt;
|- style=&amp;quot;border: 1px dashed darkgreen&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;
|style=&amp;quot;text-align:center&amp;quot;|3&lt;br /&gt;
|style=&amp;quot;text-align:right&amp;quot;|8192&lt;br /&gt;
|- style=&amp;quot;border: 1px dashed darkgreen&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;
|style=&amp;quot;text-align:center&amp;quot;|4&lt;br /&gt;
|style=&amp;quot;text-align:right&amp;quot;|4096&lt;br /&gt;
|- style=&amp;quot;border: 1px dashed darkgreen&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;
|style=&amp;quot;text-align:center&amp;quot;|5&lt;br /&gt;
|style=&amp;quot;text-align:right&amp;quot;|2048&lt;br /&gt;
|- style=&amp;quot;border: 1px dashed darkgreen&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;
|style=&amp;quot;text-align:center&amp;quot;|6&lt;br /&gt;
|style=&amp;quot;text-align:right&amp;quot;|1024&lt;br /&gt;
|- style=&amp;quot;border: 1px dashed darkgreen&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;
|style=&amp;quot;text-align:center&amp;quot;|7+&lt;br /&gt;
|style=&amp;quot;text-align:right&amp;quot;|512&lt;br /&gt;
|}&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;lt;!-- Accurate as of 0.A Kaufman --&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
If [[options|skill rust]] is turned on (Default in {{inlineVer|0.D}} is off), skills will degrade after a while without practice. Every X turns, there is a percentage chance the current practice percentage may be decremented. This chance is multiplied by 1.33 with the [[Forgetful]] trait and by 0.66 with the [[Good Memory]] trait. Skills that are displayed as red or pink have gone long enough without practice that they are in danger of rusting. If rust takes the current practice percentage below zero and the current rust setting allows level loss, the skill level will be decremented and then the practice percentage will be set to 99%.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The [[Enhanced Memory Banks]] [[bionic]] will prevent skill rust as long as power is available.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
{| class=&amp;quot;wikitable&amp;quot; |&lt;br /&gt;
