	<entry>
		<id>http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Radio_tower&amp;diff=40469</id>
		<title>Radio tower</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Radio_tower&amp;diff=40469"/>
		<updated>2022-06-18T13:30:22Z</updated>

		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Mrstickman1997: Removed obsolete sentences as radio towers are more useful for vantage points and useful items nowadays...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;div&gt;{{Terrain&lt;br /&gt;
 |name=radio tower&lt;br /&gt;
 |glyph=&amp;lt;nowiki&amp;gt;&amp;amp;&amp;lt;/nowiki&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 |color=c_ltgray&lt;br /&gt;
 |movement=0&lt;br /&gt;
 |trap=tr_null&lt;br /&gt;
 |action=none&lt;br /&gt;
 |flags=noitem&lt;br /&gt;
}}&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
A leveled field with a radio tower. The tower can be climbed via stairs or ladders depending which the tower is generated with.&lt;br /&gt;
Some towers will spawn with the Radio Shack, a pleasant place to pick up miscellaneous technical curiosities.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Climbing up a radio tower, especially with [[binoculars]], will provide unmatched overmap field of view, one may also find remains of a survivor with a [[survivor telescope]] and a [[survivor's map]].&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
{{spoiler|There is a lab computer that shows you all the current radio towers nearby, all the more better for uncovering more map space!}}&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
[[Category:Terrain]]&lt;/div&gt;</summary>
		<author><name>Mrstickman1997</name></author>
		
	</entry>
	<entry>
		<id>http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Bleeding&amp;diff=40460</id>
		<title>Bleeding</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Bleeding&amp;diff=40460"/>
		<updated>2022-06-10T13:49:45Z</updated>

		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Mrstickman1997: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;div&gt;A bleeding wound will cause the wounded body part to continually lose hit points, while leaving a bloody trail behind. If the bleeding body part is the torso or head you might eventually die from it.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The enemy most often encountered with the ability to cause this type of wounds is the common [[black bear|bear]] and [[Wolf (monster)|wolf]] (check the item browser on the [[enemies]] page and look for the ones with the BLEED flag, since {{InlineVer|0.D}} the IMPALE tag also causes bleeding).&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
An bleeding bodypart is {{igs|red|c_red}} in the interface, and shows up in the {{k|@}} player info screen as 'Bleeding (body part)'. It is usually accompanied by some [[Pain|pain]].&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
As of [[0.F (Frank)]], bleeding goes up in stages depending of the extend of the damage and losing too much blood when bleeding can also lead to stages of [[hypovolemic shock]], monsters can now bleed too, and will lose health as they bleed, so try and use one or a few bullets to inflict heavy arterial bleeding and then finish them off with melee, or simply bleed them out easier with a [[Machete]], [[Kukri]] or [[Katana]].&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
You can stop a bleeding wound in several ways:&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
* [[first aid kit]]: Stops the bleeding automatically (before 0.D Danny)&lt;br /&gt;
* [[bandage]]: Stops the bleeding automatically&lt;br /&gt;
* [[hemostatic powder]]: Stops the bleeding automatically&lt;br /&gt;
* [[rag]]: Has a chance of stopping the bleeding; returns a [[blood soaked rag]]&lt;br /&gt;
* [[cotton balls]]: Has  a chance of stopping the bleeding&lt;br /&gt;
* Cauterize with a [[soldering iron]], [[hotplate]], or both a knife (any kind) and [[lighter]]: Stops the bleeding automatically, at the cost of a steep rise in [[pain]] level.&lt;br /&gt;
* Put pressure on the wound by waiting with no weapon in hand, this prevents any further damage while doing so as long as the player is patient enough to wait a little to stop the bleeding.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
{{ver|0.F}}&lt;br /&gt;
{{Effects}}&lt;br /&gt;
[[Category:Effects]]&lt;/div&gt;</summary>
		<author><name>Mrstickman1997</name></author>
		
	</entry>
