	<entry>
		<id>http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=LMOE_shelter&amp;diff=40283</id>
		<title>LMOE shelter</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=LMOE_shelter&amp;diff=40283"/>
		<updated>2022-03-22T12:13:11Z</updated>

		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Mrstickman1997: They are good for protection from bad seasons as well as the new portal storm feature.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;lt;noinclude&amp;gt;{{Map&amp;lt;/noinclude&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;lt;includeonly&amp;gt;{{row/Map1&amp;lt;/includeonly&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 |name=LMOE shelter&lt;br /&gt;
 |glyph=&amp;lt;nowiki&amp;gt;+&amp;lt;/nowiki&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 |color=c_red&lt;br /&gt;
 |seecost=2&lt;br /&gt;
 |extras=no_extras&lt;br /&gt;
}}&amp;lt;noinclude&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
LMOE stands for Last Man On Earth. It's the kind of shelter most real-life survivalists dream of (and some of them own).&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
It has an underground area and forms an excellent shelter. It has its own water supply, in the form of a small water pond, and significant other supplies. If you get into a tight spot, it has a very defensible entrance and all doors are metal. There is a small food storage area with non-perishables as well as a handful of crates in the water area. There may also be wood-burning stoves in the water room as well as the bedroom. There is also a bathroom. You may also find equipment for survival inside, like tools. The entrance is easily distinguished from the surrounding forest, as there will be a small clearing around it, which is in turn surrounded by trees and shrubs. All in all, a wonderful place to set up for someone who wants to hide out in the forest or use this as a base for raiding nearby towns.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Being underground, LMOE shelters will also provide excellent protection from adverse weather conditions during dangerous [[season]]s such as [[summer]] and [[winter]], and will also protect from [[portal storms]] as of the current [[experimental]] version.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
[[Firearms]] can be found in LMOE shelters. In most of them as of [[0.D (Danny)]], the rooms that contain the firearms are secret rooms disguised as a typical metal wall, so try and check every wall just in case you can get those sweet guns. Moreover, any guns tend to be high-caliber, including the powerful [[Desert Eagle .44]] usable by survivors with less strength.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
As of [[0.E (Ellison)]], there are also exercise machines in LMOE shelters. These machines can be used by survivors to build up their abilities; one can decide how strenuously to exercise on these machines.&lt;br /&gt;
[[Category:Wilderness]]&lt;br /&gt;
{{Ver|0.E}}&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;lt;/noinclude&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;</summary>
		<author><name>Mrstickman1997</name></author>
		
	</entry>
