	<entry>
		<id>http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Spring_(season)&amp;diff=40279</id>
		<title>Spring (season)</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Spring_(season)&amp;diff=40279"/>
		<updated>2022-03-12T20:12:27Z</updated>

		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Mrstickman1997: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;div&gt;'''Spring''' is the first (in most [[scenarios]]), and one of the two safer seasons in Cataclysm Dark Days Ahead, alongside [[autumn]].&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Spring is followed by [[summer]], since summer is deadly for the unprepared, players should spend their first spring preparing for the harsh heat that is to come.&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;lt;noinclude&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
==[[Weather]]==&lt;br /&gt;
During the first days of this [[season]], the weather is mainly flurries, as the days pass, the flurries tend to be replaced by drizzles by the afternoon, causing relative wetness if the player hasn't got good enough protection.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The temperature during the season tends to be cold, but gets milder and eventually warm as the days get closer to [[summer]].&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Rain is a common weather occurrence during spring once the flurries die off, and thunder storms and lightning storms can occasionally happen.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
==Plants==&lt;br /&gt;
During spring, [[wild vegetables]] can be abundantly foraged from [[underbrush|underbrushes]] in [[forest]]s, [[wild herbs]], [[salsify]], [[bee balm]] and [[garlic]] can also be found.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Fruits do not grow from any bushes and trees during this season.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Early in the season, it will be too cold to plant seeds, but as the temperature warms up, [[farming]] can eventually be started.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
==Tips==&lt;br /&gt;
*See the [[The First Day|First Day Guide]] for tips on surviving the first day, which is almost always set in spring.&lt;br /&gt;
* Keep your winter clothes on during the start of the season, as it will still be relatively cold, winter clothes commonly have decent protection.&lt;br /&gt;
* A funnel is great during this season due to the abundance of rain. Don't forget to boil or purify it or risk a [[Food poisoning|food poisoning]]&lt;br /&gt;
*Try and gather or craft low warmth clothes for summer, and stockpile enough non-perishable/long lasting food and water for the later seasons, especially for winter.&lt;br /&gt;
*As the weather warms up ready for summer, change to cooler clothes so you don't [[Body temperature|overheat]].&lt;br /&gt;
*Don't bother too much eating the canned food you collect during this season, as fresh food is common enough during this season, and wild vegetables will start you off on keeping healthy. Save it for [[winter]], it's obviously not going to rot away, and you will have it ready to fall upon when dealing with health problems during winter.&lt;br /&gt;
*While drizzles are common and easy to endure with most articles of clothing in spring, the same can't be said for the occasional rain, thunder storms, and lightning storms, try and obtain a [[windbreaker]] for the early season, and a [[rain coat]] for the late season when it starts to warm up.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
[[Category:Game Mechanics]]&lt;br /&gt;
[[category:world]]&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;lt;/noinclude&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;</summary>
		<author><name>Mrstickman1997</name></author>
		
	</entry>
	<entry>
		<id>http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Vehicles&amp;diff=40191</id>
		<title>Vehicles</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Vehicles&amp;diff=40191"/>
		<updated>2022-01-23T19:22:07Z</updated>

		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Mrstickman1997: /* Default Vehicles */&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;div&gt;[[Category:Vehicles]]&lt;br /&gt;
{{sidebar/vehicles}}&lt;br /&gt;
{{tocr}}&lt;br /&gt;
Vehicles, as their name suggests, provide a means for the survivor to move around much faster than on foot and if equipped with a trunk or box; allow the survivor to store his or her belongings in them.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Unfortunately due to the loud noises their engines make, they can quickly turn into a death-trap should you cruise through a town because of the huge amount of zombies their loudness attracts. Due to [[Acid_rain|acid rain]] and perhaps the neglect of their previous owners, most of the vehicles found in the streets are either damaged or broken, and this fact can quickly lead to the demise to the unlucky-enough driver of the car should his or her car break down in the middle of a horde.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
== Common Locations ==&lt;br /&gt;
Automobiles and other kinds of vehicles can be found in many places. Towns are filled with vehicles of all kinds blocking the streets, usually wrecked. [[Garage]]s can spawn vehicles of various kinds, sometimes just chassis, but often drivable ones. [[Farm]]s have a good chance of housing a flatbed truck in decent condition. [[Road]]s contain large numbers of cars and trucks, and there's always wrecked cars next to [[gas station]]s. [[Sewage treatment]] plants and [[mall]]s usually have some vehicles in the parking area.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
While the majority of vehicles you'll find won't be of too much use other than for spare parts, make a habit of checking all the ones you find, as there's always a few that you can drive.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The first thing you want to check when finding a new vehicle is the amount of [[gasoline]] or [[battery|batteries]] left (unless it's a bicycle) and if it has enough wheels to move around. In addition, you should check that the vehicle's controls, engine, and a seat are in working condition (any color other than gray).  That information is displayed when {{key|e}}xamining the vehicle. With enough fuel and wheels you can start driving that vehicle as soon as you find it, so you can move it to a safer place to be able to enhance it, repair it, refill it, etc without the threat of zombies and other beasts.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
== Default Vehicles ==&lt;br /&gt;
This is a list of some of the vehicles that you can find in the aforementioned locations (do note that these aren't all of the vehicles you can find currently):&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
{|width=&amp;quot;70%&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;
! Bicycle&lt;br /&gt;
! Motorcycle&lt;br /&gt;
! Quad Bike&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
|-&lt;br /&gt;
