	<entry>
		<id>http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Spores_(disease)&amp;diff=40145</id>
		<title>Spores (disease)</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Spores_(disease)&amp;diff=40145"/>
		<updated>2022-01-09T15:59:09Z</updated>

		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Mrstickman1997: Removed misinformation, the 999 pain does NOT kill, but the pain and limb breaking causes awful effects that may as well have killed you...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;div&gt;[[Spores (disease)|Spores]] is a [[effects|disease]] that can be acquired while standing adjacent to [[fungaloid]]s or other fungal infected monsters without good environmental protection on your entire body (except hands and feet). Flying [[spore cloud]]s are actually harmless by themselves and do not cause this infection.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The disease has a minimal duration of 30 turns and a 3.(3)% chance per turn to settle in a character's body and grow into Fungal Parasite. Spore infection cannot be healed except with aid.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Despite the status description it actually gives a -15 [[speed]] penalty.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
== Fungal Parasite ==&lt;br /&gt;
Fungal parasites result from a successful case of spore infection, getting fungal haze in one's eyes or mouth, direct injection by fungal tendrils, or (rarely) from direct planar passage {{spoiler|0.01% per turn of telesickness}}. In contrast to other diseases, this one gets worse over time, and does not go away on its own, making it especially deadly to contract. The disease decreases the character's [[movement points]] by 10&amp;lt;!-- p.moves-=10 right in dis_effect() instead of disease_speed_boost(), need to research effects? --&amp;gt;, and strength and dexterity by 1. Fungal parasite can be detected by [[Blood Analysis]] (disease is not shown in character status screen) and cured by [[Blood Filter]] bionics, [[antifungal drug]], or (not guaranteed to work) [[fungicide]].&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
First hour symptoms: &lt;br /&gt;
* Heavy coughing ([[noise]] of 12) and [[Pain|pain]] +1 with 0.6% chance per turn (0.3% for characters with [[traits#Poison Resistant|Poison Resistant]]).&lt;br /&gt;
* Messages about nausea or taste of mushrooms, both with 1% chance per turn (0.5% for PR).&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
One to six hours symptoms:&lt;br /&gt;
* Spasm, which hurts torso for 5 HP and takes out 100 movement points, with 0.1(6)% chance per turn (0.(1)% with Poison Resistant).&lt;br /&gt;
* Distinctive vomiting (described as &amp;quot;vomiting a thick gray goop&amp;quot;), which takes out 200 movement points and adds 50 [[hunger]] and 68 thirst, with a 0.05% chance (0.6% with [[traits#Weak Stomach|Weak Stomach]], or 0.125% chance with [[mutation#Nausea|Nausea]]) per turn (0.02%, 0.04%, or 0.07% with Poison Resistant).&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Full symptoms (after 6 hours):&lt;br /&gt;
* Fungaloid spores coughing, which takes out 500 movement points and happens silently (in contrary to monsters variant), with 0.01% chance per turn (0.0(5)% with Poison Resistant).&lt;br /&gt;
* Fungus breaks both arms (no matter their hp) and causes 999 pain with 0.1(6)% chance per turn (0.0125% with Poison Resistant). While this does NOT kill the player, the pain makes them barely able to move quickly, brings down all their stats to 0 and disallows them from holding weapons.&lt;br /&gt;
{{Effects}}&lt;br /&gt;
[[Category:Effects]]&lt;br /&gt;
[[Category:Diseases]]&lt;/div&gt;</summary>
		<author><name>Mrstickman1997</name></author>
		
	</entry>
	<entry>
		<id>http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Pain&amp;diff=40144</id>
		<title>Pain</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Pain&amp;diff=40144"/>
		<updated>2022-01-09T15:55:13Z</updated>

		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Mrstickman1997: Fungal parasites increase it by 999 in late stage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;div&gt;There are 9 perceivable levels of pain:&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
* No pain&lt;br /&gt;
* Minimal pain&lt;br /&gt;
* Mild pain&lt;br /&gt;
* Moderate pain&lt;br /&gt;
* Distracting pain&lt;br /&gt;
* Distressing pain&lt;br /&gt;
* Unmanageable pain&lt;br /&gt;
* Intense pain&lt;br /&gt;
* Severe pain&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
High levels of pain can result in stat penalties.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
'''How does it increase?''' (Not a complete list)&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
* By taking damage from enemies&lt;br /&gt;
* Walking over certain tiles such as rubble or fire&lt;br /&gt;
* Diseases or conditions such as infected bite wounds&lt;br /&gt;
* Failed implanting of bionics&lt;br /&gt;
* Certain weather such as acid rain&lt;br /&gt;
* Rapid physiological changes from [[mutation]] can be painful&lt;br /&gt;
* Being overburdened (can easily result from strength being lowered due to pain)&lt;br /&gt;
* Having one's arms broken by a late stage [[fungal parasite]], causing 999 pain&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
'''How does it decrease?'''&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
* Waiting for it to go down (Taking painkillers speeds up this process)&lt;br /&gt;
* Using Bionics&lt;br /&gt;
* Adrenaline can temporarily alleviate the effects of pain&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
(Certain mutations also speed up pain loss and resistance to pain)&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
== Painkillers ==&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
'''Painkiller''' is a value indicating internal effects working against pain.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Default value: 0 | Max value: 240&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
'''How does it increase?'''&lt;br /&gt;
* By taking certain [[Comestibles/Meds|Meds]]&lt;br /&gt;
* By drinking [[alcohol]] (stronger is better), unless you [[Alcohol Metabolism|metabolize it]]&lt;br /&gt;
* Tiny amounts can be gained by smoking [[Cannabis|weed]]&lt;br /&gt;
* Traits like [[Chemical Imbalance]] and [[Schizophrenic]] can randomly increase it&lt;br /&gt;
* If negative, it will increase by 1 every 5 minutes&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
'''How does it decrease?'''&lt;br /&gt;
* If positive, it will decrease by 1 every 5 minutes&lt;br /&gt;
* Addiction to painkillers (1 per turn at 25+ intensity, otherwise 1 per (100 - 4 * intensity) turns)&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
'''Effects'''&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
It is subtracted from pain in pretty much every situation where pain is involved in any way.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Kills you instantly if you get it above 240.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Decreases speed, but less so than the pain it prevents would cause.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
'''Maximum painkiller effect'''&lt;br /&gt;
* aspirin - 15&lt;br /&gt;
* codeine - 49&lt;br /&gt;
* heroin - 92&lt;br /&gt;
* morphine - 62&lt;br /&gt;
*oxycodone - 62&lt;br /&gt;
* poppy painkiller - 47&lt;br /&gt;
* tramadol - 40&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
