		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Mrstickman1997: Added a description for the Mycus tree, with Mycus lingo...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;div&gt;{{spoilers}}&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
{{:mycus}}&lt;br /&gt;
Remember the [[fungal bloom]]s, [[fungal flowers]] and [[fungal tower]]s you encountered? Well, you have now joined us, humanity will call you a traitor, but we know better, welcome to the [[fungi|fungal family]]...&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The threshold mutation of this category is called '''''[[Mycus]]''''' ingame.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
We contain spoilers.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
{{Mutationthresholds/Mycus}}&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
[[Guide:_Mycus|We look here.]]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
{{spoiler|The &amp;quot;threshold&amp;quot; mutation, Mycus, is gained through steps mentioned in the above guide. Further mutations in the Mycus category are unlocked during sleep and when consuming mycus fruits.}}&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
{{spoiler|Mycus mutations cancel out all &amp;quot;standard&amp;quot; mutations (Alpha, Spider, etc.); you cannot use mutations from other categories.}}&lt;br /&gt;
