	<entry>
		<id>http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Military_base&amp;diff=40011</id>
		<title>Military base</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Military_base&amp;diff=40011"/>
		<updated>2021-09-08T22:09:15Z</updated>

		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Mrstickman1997: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;lt;noinclude&amp;gt;{{Map&amp;lt;/noinclude&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;lt;includeonly&amp;gt;{{row/Map1&amp;lt;/includeonly&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 |name=military base&lt;br /&gt;
 |glyph=&amp;lt;nowiki&amp;gt;M&amp;lt;/nowiki&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 |color=c_red&lt;br /&gt;
 |extras=no_extras&lt;br /&gt;
}}&amp;lt;noinclude&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Once a proud home to the once-powerful U.S Military, these colossal and well-guarded bases were unfortunately overrun by the [[Zombies|zombie hordes]], and are now filled with deadly military zombies such as [[zombie soldier]]s, [[zombie burner]]s, and more.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Compared to the smaller military outposts, military bases are a LOT more rarer and larger but are the mother-lode for high quality loot; plenty of ammo, [[firearms]] including [[grenade launchers]] MREs, medical supplies, military uniforms and more.&lt;br /&gt;
These bases are surrounded by [[land mine]]s, so one should be careful if they are planning to enter these bases.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
This is the starting location for the [[Overrun]] scenario.&lt;/div&gt;</summary>
		<author><name>Mrstickman1997</name></author>
		
	</entry>
