	<entry>
		<id>http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Light_amp_goggles&amp;diff=39982</id>
		<title>Light amp goggles</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Light_amp_goggles&amp;diff=39982"/>
		<updated>2021-08-30T11:51:34Z</updated>

		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Mrstickman1997: /* Notes */ Added how useful these goggles are.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;lt;noinclude&amp;gt;{{Clothes&amp;lt;/noinclude&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;lt;includeonly&amp;gt;{{row/Clothing1&amp;lt;/includeonly&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 |name=light amp goggles&lt;br /&gt;
 |glyph=&amp;lt;nowiki&amp;gt;[&amp;lt;/nowiki&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 |color=c_cyan&lt;br /&gt;
 |volume=3&lt;br /&gt;
 |weight=1020&lt;br /&gt;
 |bash=1&lt;br /&gt;
 |cut=0&lt;br /&gt;
 |tohit=-2&lt;br /&gt;
 |rarity=0&lt;br /&gt;
 |price=920&lt;br /&gt;
 |mat1=steel&lt;br /&gt;
 |mat2=glass&lt;br /&gt;
 |func=&lt;br /&gt;
 |encumber=2&lt;br /&gt;
 |storage=0&lt;br /&gt;
 |bashprotect=0&lt;br /&gt;
 |cutprotect=0&lt;br /&gt;
 |enviprotect=6&lt;br /&gt;
 |warmth=20&lt;br /&gt;
 |covers1=EYES&lt;br /&gt;
 |description=A pair of goggles that amplify ambient light, allowing you to see in the dark.  You must be carrying a powered-on unified power supply, or UPS, to use them.&lt;br /&gt;
 |coverage=95&lt;br /&gt;
 |thickness=2&lt;br /&gt;
 |image=[[File:Idz.jpg|thumb|A German Army soldier with a &amp;quot;LUCIE&amp;quot; night vision.]]&lt;br /&gt;
}}&amp;lt;noinclude&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
== Notes ==&lt;br /&gt;
*If you manage to find this and some batteries for it, you have hit quite a milestone and jackpot, as this item allows you to [[Night Raids: Guide|sneak into cities at night]] without [[zombies]] easily noticing; going into the city during the daytime is basically inviting zombies to dinner unless you have the means to [[clearing the city|clear them out of the city]], and most [[firearms]] are more likely to be found in the city anyway...&lt;br /&gt;
*This may be surprising, but taking these goggles into the sewers and subway tracks is actually more dangerous than bringing a flashlight, as many of the monsters that dwell down in these areas; [[sewer rat]]s, [[seweranha]]s, and [[sewer snake]]s have night vision, but can't see well when the player brings a flashlight near them.&lt;br /&gt;
*Just remember, this item is useful for sneaking and stealthy attacks; fighting against a horde head-on with these valuable goggles on will lead to them breaking as they are fragile, do you really want to lose them in the middle of a zombie infested city?&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
