Also, using a light in the [[sewer]]s and [[subway]]s can cause creatures such as [[sewer rat]]s, [[sewer snakes]] and [[seweranha]]s to become short sighted, as they have night vision, but no vision in the light, so it may be worth it to bring a flashlight down these areas even if the player has night vision equipment and abilities.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
It uses one charge every 20 moves.{{verify|&amp;lt;!--is this still 20 moves? or now due to the time change 120 turns?--&amp;gt;}}&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
{{footer/electronics}}&lt;br /&gt;
{{Tools}}&lt;br /&gt;
[[Category:Tools]][[Category:Components]]&lt;br /&gt;
[[Category:electronics]]&lt;br /&gt;
{{ver|0.E}}&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;lt;/noinclude&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;</summary>
		<author><name>Mrstickman1997</name></author>
		
	</entry>
	<entry>
		<id>http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Challenge-Abandoned&amp;diff=39972</id>
		<title>Challenge-Abandoned</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Challenge-Abandoned&amp;diff=39972"/>
		<updated>2021-08-25T11:54:40Z</updated>

		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Mrstickman1997: /* Notes */ Added notes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;lt;noinclude&amp;gt;{{Infobox/scenario&amp;lt;/noinclude&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;lt;includeonly&amp;gt;{{Row/scenario&amp;lt;/includeonly&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 |name=Challenge-Abandoned&lt;br /&gt;
 |start_name=Hospital&lt;br /&gt;
 |ident=patient&lt;br /&gt;
 |points=-8&lt;br /&gt;
 |allowed_professions1=unemployed&lt;br /&gt;
 |allowed_professions2=bionic_patient&lt;br /&gt;
 |allowed_professions3=patient&lt;br /&gt;
 |allowed_professions4=broken_cyborg&lt;br /&gt;
 |restricted_professions1=&lt;br /&gt;
 |allowed_locs1=[[Hospital]]&lt;br /&gt;
 |map_special=&lt;br /&gt;
 |forced_traits1=FLIMSY2&lt;br /&gt;
 |forbidden_traits1=TOUGH&lt;br /&gt;
 |forbidden_traits2=DISRESISTANT&lt;br /&gt;
 |flags1=CHALLENGE&lt;br /&gt;
 |description=Sickly and frail, you have spent most of your life in the patient's ward of the hospital.  When yours was evacuated, you were left behind because you were a lost cause.  You awaken to the sound of movement around the hospital.&lt;br /&gt;
}}&amp;lt;noinclude&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
==Notes==&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;lt;!-- *YOUR PERSONAL NOTES AND HINTS GO BELOW HERE* --&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
*There are many exits within the [[hospital]], the main entrance however is likely to be surrounded by [[zombies]], so a player may want to avoid exiting via that way; instead the player may want to opt for exiting via the fire exits, where there may be no zombies at all upon exiting. Just try and keep quiet as possible as you move throughout the hospital, and never let the zombies corner you into any rooms, as it is a swift death with lack of equipment and the [[Frail]] trait.&lt;br /&gt;
*If you do escape the hospital, you are not out of the fire yet, as you are still in the city, you may want to either wait until night in a safe place to sneak out of the city, or survive in the city itself if you are lucky enough to find a good building for shelter and inconspicuousness.&lt;br /&gt;
*Another problem; you always start the scenario with the Frail trait, luckily however, you can mutate with the correct mutation trees to override this trait with the [[Resilient]] trait, the [[Medical]] mutation tree is best for this as it is low risk, medium to high award.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
[[Category:scenario]]&lt;br /&gt;
{{footer/scenarios}}&lt;br /&gt;
{{ver|0.D}}&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;lt;/noinclude&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;</summary>
		<author><name>Mrstickman1997</name></author>
		
	</entry>
	<entry>
		<id>http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Royal_jelly&amp;diff=39969</id>
		<title>Royal jelly</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Royal_jelly&amp;diff=39969"/>
		<updated>2021-08-24T14:16:58Z</updated>

		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Mrstickman1997: You obviously haven't looked at the item browser, the health stat is what helps healing and prevents disease for the most part...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;lt;includeonly&amp;gt;{{Template:Row/Food&amp;lt;/includeonly&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;lt;noinclude&amp;gt;{{Food&amp;lt;/noinclude&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 |name=royal jelly&lt;br /&gt;
 |id=royal_jelly&lt;br /&gt;
 |glyph=&amp;lt;nowiki&amp;gt;%&amp;lt;/nowiki&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 |color=white&lt;br /&gt;
 |volume=1&lt;br /&gt;
 |weight=150&lt;br /&gt;
 |bash=0&lt;br /&gt;
 |cut=0&lt;br /&gt;
 |tohit=0&lt;br /&gt;
 |rarity=0&lt;br /&gt;
 |price=400&lt;br /&gt;
 |mat1=veggy&lt;br /&gt;
 |mat2=MNULL&lt;br /&gt;
 |func=&lt;br /&gt;
 |charges=1&lt;br /&gt;
 |container=itm_null&lt;br /&gt;
 |quench=0&lt;br /&gt;
 |nutrition=10&lt;br /&gt;
 |spoils=0&lt;br /&gt;
 |stim=0&lt;br /&gt;
 |health=1&lt;br /&gt;
 |addiction=0&lt;br /&gt;
 |addictiontype=none&lt;br /&gt;
 |fun=-5&lt;br /&gt;
 |flags=EDIBLE_FROZEN, NUTRIENT_OVERRIDE&lt;br /&gt;
 |description=A translucent hexagonal chunk of wax, filled with dense, milky, bitter and acidic-tasting jelly. Though some hold it as a panacea, it doesn't have any medical benefit. Still it is rich with the most beneficial substances the hive can produce.&lt;br /&gt;
}}&amp;lt;noinclude&amp;gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
== Notes ==&lt;br /&gt;
This substance is baby bee food created in the head of a nurse bee.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
All larva bees are fed royal jelly for three days and the diet then changes according to what the workers decide the bee should be. (Royal jelly for queens, a 1-1 mix of pollen and honey for workers, and a 3 pollen 1 honey mix for drones.)&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
This item used to be a cure-all for many diseases, but as of [[0.E (Ellison)]], that use was removed from this item and replaced with a rare drug called [[Panaceus]].&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
While royal jelly is now pretty useless by itself now, it can still be used to cook a very healthy and filling recipe called [[royal beef]], which increases the player's [[health]] stat by 10.&lt;br /&gt;
[[Category:Comestibles]]&lt;br /&gt;
{{Ver|0.F}}&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;lt;/noinclude&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;</summary>
		<author><name>Mrstickman1997</name></author>
		
	</entry>
	<entry>
		<id>http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Zombie/doc&amp;diff=39876</id>
		<title>Zombie/doc</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://cddawiki.chezzo.com/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Zombie/doc&amp;diff=39876"/>
		<updated>2021-08-10T13:48:14Z</updated>

		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Mrstickman1997: Added a little on their Dark Skies Above counterpart.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;div&gt;* While relatively basic and weak, being common, they are the most common vector of [[infection]]s. Fighting zombies too much early in the game without any infection treatment puts the player at risk, as one bite can end up being fatal. Avoiding zombies as long as possible until an infection treatment is procured is recommended.&lt;br /&gt;
* Turns into a [[Tough zombie]] if it's near a [[Zombie master]].&lt;br /&gt;
* In the [[Dark Skies Above]] mod, these zombies are replaced by the [[Stray]], which is quite similar in behaviour, though is a little weaker HP wise and faster in movement than it's vanilla counterpart.&lt;/div&gt;</summary>
		<author><name>Mrstickman1997</name></author>
		
	</entry>
